(506, 126, 'mfn-page-items-seo', '<br />\r\n\r\n<p class=\"big\" style=\"font-size:120%;\">The credit growth in the micro, small and medium enterprises (MSME) sector is improving, with the overall exposure reaching the highest level in over a year, says MSME Pulse QuarterlyReport by Transunion CIBIL-SIDBI. The overall credit exposure has shown the highest growth in last five quarters at  Rs 54.20 trillion as on March 31, 2018, with MSMEs  constituting Rs 12.6 trillion(23 per cent) of the commercial credit outstanding.</p>\r\n<p class=\"big\" style=\"font-size:120%;\">The Business Standard, New Delhi, 21st June 2018</p>\n\n'),
